description:
If tenant has Telegram bot configured (bot token + chat ID in settings):

After order is created, call Telegram Bot API via edge function:
POST https://api.telegram.org/bot{token}/sendMessage
chat_id: {chatId}
text: formatted order details:

"🛒 New Order #{orderNumber}
Customer: {name}
Phone: {phone}
Contact via: {preferredMethod}

Items:
- {productName} x{qty} — ${lineTotal}

Subtotal: ${subtotal}
Tax: ${tax}
Delivery: ${deliveryFee}
Total: ${total}

Payment: {paymentMethod}
Fulfillment: {delivery/pickup}
Address: {address}
Notes: {notes}"

Create edge function: forward-order-telegram/index.ts
If bot token not set: skip. If API fails: log error, don't fail order.

After order creation:
UPDATE products SET stock_quantity = stock_quantity - {qty}
WHERE id = {productId} AND stock_quantity >= {qty}
Check affected rows. If 0 rows affected: product went out of stock 
between validation and deduction (race condition).
Handle: rollback order or mark as needing attention.

Create PostgreSQL function if it doesn't exist:

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION deduct_stock(
  p_product_id UUID,
  p_quantity INTEGER
) RETURNS BOOLEAN
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
SET search_path = public
AS $$
DECLARE
  affected INTEGER;
BEGIN
  UPDATE products 
  SET stock_quantity = stock_quantity - p_quantity
  WHERE id = p_product_id 
  AND stock_quantity >= p_quantity;

  GET DIAGNOSTICS affected = ROW_COUNT;
  RETURN affected > 0;
END;
$$;

This atomically deducts stock and returns false if insufficient.

Atomic order number generation:

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION next_order_number(p_tenant_id UUID)
RETURNS INTEGER
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER SET search_path = public AS $$
DECLARE
  next_num INTEGER;
BEGIN
  SELECT COALESCE(MAX(order_number), 1000) + 1
  INTO next_num
  FROM orders
  WHERE tenant_id = p_tenant_id;
  RETURN next_num;
END;
$$;
